hands_on_practices.solution:
We have the traceless rate-of-strain tensor for an incompressible shear flow $\mathbf v=v_x(y)\,\hat{\mathbf x}$:
$$W_{ij}=\frac{\partial v_i}{\partial x_j}+\frac{\partial v_j}{\partial x_i}-\frac{2}{3}(\nabla\cdot\mathbf v)\,\delta_{ij}
\;\Rightarrow\;
W_{xy}=W_{yx}=\frac{dv_x}{dy},\quad W_{xx}=W_{yy}=W_{zz}=0.$$

The projection of $\mathbf W$ along $\hat{\mathbf b}=(\cos\theta,\sin\theta,0)$ is
$$\hat b_iW_{ij}\hat b_j
=2\,b_xb_y\,\frac{dv_x}{dy}
=2\cos\theta\,\sin\theta\,\frac{dv_x}{dy}
=\sin(2\theta)\,\frac{dv_x}{dy}.$$

Thus the parallel stress tensor is
$$\Pi_{\|\,ij}
=-3\eta_0\Bigl(\hat b_kW_{k\ell}\hat b_\ell\Bigr)\Bigl(b_ib_j-\frac{1}{3}\delta_{ij}\Bigr)
=-3\eta_0\,\sin(2\theta)\,\frac{dv_x}{dy}\,\Bigl(b_ib_j-\frac{1}{3}\delta_{ij}\Bigr).$$

The viscous force is $\mathbf{F}_v = -\nabla \cdot \mathbf{\Pi}_{\|}$. Taking the divergence and using $d^2v_x/dy^2=C$ gives
$$F_i = - \frac{\partial}{\partial x_j} \Pi_{\|\,i j} = -\frac{\partial}{\partial y}\Pi_{\|\,i y}
= - \left[-3\eta_0\,\sin(2\theta)\,C\,\Bigl(b_i b_y-\frac{1}{3}\delta_{i y}\Bigr)\right] = 3\eta_0\,\sin(2\theta)\,C\,\Bigl(b_i b_y-\frac{1}{3}\delta_{i y}\Bigr).$$

Finally the component along $\hat{\mathbf b}$ is
$$\mathbf F_v\cdot\hat{\mathbf b}
=F_i\,b_i
=3\eta_0\,\sin(2\theta)\,C\Bigl(b_y(b_i b_i)-\frac{1}{3}(\delta_{iy}b_i)\Bigr)
=3\eta_0\,\sin(2\theta)\,C\Bigl(b_y-\frac{1}{3}b_y\Bigr)
=2\eta_0\,\sin(2\theta)\,b_y\,C
=4\eta_0\,C\,\sin^2\theta\,\cos\theta.$$
